definitions.text: a canonical hour that is the ninth hour of the day counting from sunrise
a service in the Roman Catholic Church formerly read or chanted at 3 PM (the ninth hour counting from sunrise) but now somewhat earlier

examples: thou shalt have none other gods before me

definitions.text: not at all or in no way
examples: seemed none too pleased with his dinner
shirt looked none the worse for having been slept in
the passage is none too clear
